  "text": "Before proving the proposition, we need some well-known lemmas (see [CITATION_1] , Chapter 1 and 2). Lemma 2.3. Let I ⊂ S and w ∈ D =I . Then there is a unique x ∈ X I such that w = xw 0,I , where w 0,I is the longest element of W I .",
